This paper deals with the design and analysis of quorum systems for replicated services in the presence of Byzantine and benign failures. This topic is closely related to distributed computing (cs.DC), cryptography (cs.CR), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), control systems (cs.SY), and information theory (cs.IT). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper, with cs.DC being the most likely due to the focus on distributed systems.
